items.summary: Include both (a) short attributed insights/quotes and (b) general summaries inspired by public high-performance figures, covering: Wim Hof, David Goggins, Shawn Ryan, Joe Rogan, Tom Brady, Michael Jordan, Mike Tyson, and Jocko Willink. Do not include copyrighted or unverifiable verbatim quotes; use paraphrased, attribution-style statements (e.g., “Inspired by …”).

Add at least one new reflection prompt to the same existing module so users can start a guided journal entry from the module, with `prefillTitle` and `prefillContent` specifically tailored to applying stress-vs-distress concepts and influencer-inspired practices.

Add new stress-related learning content (stress vs. distress / eustress vs. distress) as additional content inside an existing learning module in `frontend/src/content/modules.ts` (do not create a new module).
